                            Researcher Calvin's Personnel File
                        </div>
                    

                    

                    



                    <div id="page-content">
                        

<div style="text-align: right;"><div class="page-rate-widget-box"><span class="rate-points">rating:&nbsp;<span class="number prw54353">+68</span></span><span class="rateup btn btn-default"><a title="I like it" href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.modules.PageRateWidgetModule.listeners.rate(event, 1)">+</a></span><span class="ratedown btn btn-default"><a title="I don't like it" href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.modules.PageRateWidgetModule.listeners.rate(event, -1)">&#8211;</a></span><span class="cancel btn btn-default"><a title="Cancel my vote" href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.modules.PageRateWidgetModule.listeners.cancelVote(event)">x</a></span></div></div>
<p><iframe src="/not-a-seagull/html/8f60aabc6140bfc3a801a8daf9ef310b24bcb31c-1587521031741047412" allowtransparency="true" frameborder="0" class="html-block-iframe"></iframe></p>
<div class="scp-image-block block-right" style="width:300px;"><img src="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/not-a-seagull/seagull.jpg" style="width:300px;" alt="seagull.jpg" class="image" />
<div class="scp-image-caption" style="width:300px;">
<p>This is not a picture of Researcher Calvin.</p>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>ADDENDUM:</strong> SCP Files</p>
<p>The following is a list of SCP files that Researcher Calvin has written. Researcher Calvin has granted other personnel permission to link to these reports in the process of writing their own.</p>
<div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-2785">SCP-2785</a> - Self Replicating Automaton - Rating: +169</strong><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><em>Wait! You have yet to see the magic of long division!</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;COMMENTARY</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;COMMENTARY</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>This was my first SCP that stayed on the mainsite. I had an SCP before this (in the same slot) about how there was a civilization of people trapped within the Saturn Hexagon by a witch or something, but it was deleted. I also had numerous other SCP ideas and drafts that were crushed by my newfound knowledge about which concepts worked. Can we get an F in chat?</p>
<p>Originally, it followed a very cliche structure: after it learned about electronics, it became evil and jaded. Thankfully, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirens" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2802387); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2802387&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609440952" alt="Sirens" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2802387)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirens" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2802387); return false;">Sirens</a></span> convinced me it was a bad idea. The naive personality came later, and eventually became the whole thing. There also used to be some weird connection to <a href="/scp-094">SCP-094</a> that no longer exists.</p>
<p>This one was plateaued at +20 for a while before I wrote its tales. I do want to go back and fix some of the dialogue on this eventually. However, part of me wants to keep it the way it is, as a &quot;museum piece&quot; or sorts.</p>
<p>In my head, SCP-2785-1 is some powerful ancient artifact that the dude accidentally trapped himself inside of. But that was so long ago that I don't remember what I had in mind originally. You decide what it is.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-3747">SCP-3747</a> - Death by Vacuum - Rating: +119</strong><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><em>That's all I needed to hear.</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;COMMENTARY</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;COMMENTARY</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Between 2785 and this one was a very, very bad SCP about an invisible demon that ate people's brains. After that one got deleted, I actually straight-up left the site for a while. Fortunately, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/shaggydredlocks" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1722371); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1722371&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609440952" alt="Shaggydredlocks" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1722371)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/shaggydredlocks" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1722371); return false;">Shaggydredlocks</a></span> convinced me to come back by offering to co-author a rewrite on that SCP. That one's still in the abyss (and it probably will be forever, considering shaggy's recent departure from the site).</p>
<p>This SCP began when I saw that you could use HTML in SCPs from <a href="/scp-3125">SCP-3125</a>. There were a lot of things I did wrong on this one. The format screw was actually written before the actual article. Although the phenomenon was grounded in real science, it goes so far into psuedoscience at some points that it seems like fantasy. The dialogue is wooden and the format screw is definitely done better in <a class="newpage" href="/scp-23177">SCP-23177</a>, with less annoying stuff. It really puzzles me how this one hasn't been deleted yet.</p>
<p>Like 2785, this is on my &quot;go back and rewrite&quot; list. But considering how long it is, that would be quite a bit of work for something that's probably flawed on the conceptual level.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-3095">SCP-3095</a> - Bird is the Word - Rating: +258</strong><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><em>SCP-3095-1 were first discovered in New York City, after an organized group made up of pigeons attempted to claim the Statue of Liberty for themselves.</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;COMMENTARY</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;COMMENTARY</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>I think SCP-3095 represents one of my greatest idiosyncrasies when it comes to SCP writing. I wrote 3747 over the better portion of three months, and it's one of the worst ones I've ever written. Meanwhile, I spent a week on this SCP, and it's my highest rated as of the time of writing. I also consider it to be one of the first that I really did a good job on.</p>
<p>The idea actually predates SCP-2785; I found an old piece of notebook paper with an early version of this one on it. The format screw came to me while I was brainstorming, although in the end it was probably unnecessary.</p>
<p>To be honest, the reason why it is rated so high is because of its tales in Team Bird. I do consider it a good representation of my work, however. And no, not just because of my name.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-3733">SCP-3733</a> - Everybody Else - Rating: +277</strong><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><em>Could you please elaborate on &quot;everybody else?&quot;</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;COMMENTARY</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;COMMENTARY</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>This one was originally going to be a multi-article epic, with exploration logs and interviews and teleporters and the like. However, I eventually wrote the first article, which was short and just had an interview, and I said &quot;well, this is good.&quot;</p>
<p>In my opinion, this is the best SCP I have written. It's short, it's effective, it goes in, does what it needs to, then gets out, and leaves holes for the reader to fill their imagination with without making the reader hunger for more too much.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-3833">SCP-3833</a> - Welcome to the Top of the Mountain - Rating: +66</strong><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><em>It's not the storm, it's the mountain. The mountain</em> hates.</p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div><div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-3248">SCP-3248</a> - Who Shot Sulley? (JamCon 2018 Entry) - Rating: +44</strong><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><em>His cadaver was later found in a nearby river. Cause of death could not be determined.</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div><div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-3485">SCP-3485</a> - Omega Messier - Rating: +80</strong><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><em>Aside from these modifications, SCP-3485 has the same systems as a non-anomalous lobster, although scaled up by several magnitudes.</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div><div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-3296">SCP-3296</a> - The Drifter (DoomsdayCon 2018 Entry) - Rating: +96</strong><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><em>god is dead and birds killed him</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;COMMENTARY</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;COMMENTARY</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>My first entry into the Doomsday Contest for Team Bird. To be honest, I don't really like this one. It's a flimsy idea designed pretty much exclusively to do what Join the Flock already does better. It went through quite a few iterations and the final product kind of mutated quite a bit from its original form.</p>
<p>However, it does what it does well, and I think it's kind of a quarterstone of Team Bird. So up it stays.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-3362">SCP-3362</a> - A Forced Self-Insert (DoomsdayCon 2018 Entry) - Rating: +138</strong><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><em>However, it is believed that this event had implications that are not within the grasp of the current Foundation.</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;COMMENTARY</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;COMMENTARY</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>The better Team Bird skip, IMO. Written entirely on my cell phone while taking vacation on a lake. The funny thing is that it isn't really a Team Bird SCP up until the last few paragraphs. Figures, right?</p>
<p>I consider this one of my better ones primarily because of how it executes a difficult idea in a fun way. However, I think there's room for improvement.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-4800">SCP-4800</a> - Midnight (4k Contest 2018 Entry) - Rating: +230</strong><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><em>What can you tell us, about, well, what's happening out there?</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;COMMENTARY</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;COMMENTARY</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>My 4kon entry, and also one of my better SCPs. I went through about 3 history-related themes before I arrived at what I have here. This was actually supposed to be a piece starting a whole series about the Multiversal Foundation Alliance and building off of that. However, I never really committed to the idea, so I think this will stay a solo piece.</p>
<p>The main problem with the SCP is that it explicitly requires the reader to deduce something in order for them to fully enjoy it. That means that you'll have a lot of people who don't even notice the actual ending. I figure it's a sacrifice that I'm willing to make for providing a puzzle for the enlightened reader.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-4799">SCP-4799</a> - Mariachi's Merchants - Rating: +72</strong><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><em>We're tech smugglers. Like I said, there's a lot of different universes out there, not just this backwater hole-in-the-ground.</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div><div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-4048">SCP-4048</a> - We need to talk about your forklift certification - Rating: +165</strong><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><em>All it did was ask me a bunch 'a' weird questions about my job. Stuff like &quot;when was the last time you went uphill on a diagonal&quot;, or &quot;have you ever moved your forklift when it's in gear&quot;.</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;COMMENTARY</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;COMMENTARY</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Saw a meme. Turned it into an SCP. There's not much else to say other than it's the ultimate proofs that meme SCPs are more successful.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-4948">SCP-4948</a> - Behind Ajar Doors - Rating: +125</strong><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><em>Attempts to remove these doors from the chamber have failed. The chamber has since been filled with concrete.</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div><div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-4148">SCP-4148</a> - Space Ladybugs (Bright's 1st Challenge Entry) - Rating: +63</strong><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><em>This was met with an erratic period of activity from SCP-4148-1 presumed to be celebration.</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div><div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-4248">SCP-4248</a> - Alphabet and Omega - Rating: +126</strong><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><em>Convince me otherwise, but I don't think God has two wings or caws.</em></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div><div class="list-pages-box">    <div class="list-pages-item">


<p><strong><a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-4348">SCP-4348</a> - dado borger and france fry - Rating: +173</strong><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><em>dado beat out competition by give dado borger and france fry before other competitors by deliver burger faster. No more fast than in the past. You already trust dado.</em></p>
