<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;COMMENTARY</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>My first and highest rated rewrite began with a rather bad article by a user about a magic theater where odd creatures watched worlds like television shows. My SCP doesn't have much in common with that one, aside from being a theater that could be accessed from the internet.</p>
<p>It was originally a Wondertainment SCP; however, it was made better without that connection. Randall was originally just really angry that the Foundation drove away all of his customers; however, making him introspective instead really helped him strike a chord with the audience, I feel.</p>
<p>This one was my highest rated for a good period of time. <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mayd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1422059); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1422059&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609440952" alt="MayD" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1422059)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mayd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1422059); return false;">MayD</a></span> even told me it was in their top ten SCPs, which is awesome. I don't really plan on writing any more Happiness Factory SCPs; not out of any fatigue, just that every time I try I just run into similarities with Wondertainment.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
